# Backend context

The Ark Notify backend lives in the sibling workspace folder `ark-notify` (path: `../`).
Before implementing API calls, auth, WebSocket, or SSE features, read:

- `ark-notify/docs/API.md` — full API reference
- `ark-notify/README.md` — architecture and quick start
- `ark-notify/src/routes/api.js` — route definitions

## Conventions

- Base URL (local): `http://localhost:3000`
- Control plane auth: JWT (`Authorization: Bearer <token>`)
- Data plane auth: `X-App-Key` + `X-App-Secret` headers
- WebSocket: `/app/:appKey?clientId=...`

Do not import backend source into the React app. Call the REST/WebSocket API only.

